00:00:39.900 --> 00:00:42.182
On the 17th of January, 1995

00:00:42.182 --> 00:00:45.150
at 5:46 in the morning,
an earthquake struck

00:00:45.150 --> 00:00:47.430
the city of Kobe Japan.

00:00:47.430 --> 00:00:50.043
It took everyone by surprise.

00:00:55.260 --> 00:00:58.050
Japan is one of the most
seismically active countries

00:00:58.050 --> 00:00:58.883
in the world.

00:00:58.883 --> 00:01:01.470
It sits on the boundary
of four tectonic plates

00:01:01.470 --> 00:01:03.750
and 90% of all earthquakes,

00:01:03.750 --> 00:01:05.700
and almost all of the powerful ones

00:01:05.700 --> 00:01:08.193
happen at tectonic plate boundaries.

00:01:09.060 --> 00:01:11.193
But Kobe isn't near one.

00:01:12.150 --> 00:01:15.000
This earthquake was caused
by an interplate fault,

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:17.610
essentially a crack in the Earth's surface

00:01:17.610 --> 00:01:20.640
that isn't at the boundary
of a tectonic plate.

00:01:20.640 --> 00:01:22.680
This fault hadn't produced any earthquakes

00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:25.500
for around a thousand years,

00:01:25.500 --> 00:01:28.813
so the city was completely unprepared.

00:01:28.813 --> 00:01:33.300
(woman speaking in Japanese)

00:01:33.300 --> 00:01:36.390
The quake measured a magnitude 6.9

00:01:36.390 --> 00:01:39.660
just under the definition
of a major earthquake.

00:01:39.660 --> 00:01:43.350
Despite this, the earthquake
killed more than 6,000 people

00:01:43.350 --> 00:01:46.680
and left another 300,000 homeless.

00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:49.650
More than 80% of the
fatalities were caused

00:01:49.650 --> 00:01:51.780
by the collapse of buildings.

00:01:51.780 --> 00:01:53.880
The total economic cost was estimated

00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:56.850
at 80 billion US dollars.

00:01:56.850 --> 00:01:58.980
