00:04:19.650 --> 00:04:21.150
- [Derek] At the center of E-Defense

00:04:21.150 --> 00:04:23.820
is a 20 meter by 15 meter shake table,

00:04:23.820 --> 00:04:26.430
which weighs 800 tons.

00:04:26.430 --> 00:04:28.860
On each side there are
five hydraulic actuators,

00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:31.020
which push the table side to side,

00:04:31.020 --> 00:04:32.370
and the whole thing is supported

00:04:32.370 --> 00:04:35.070
by another 14 actuators at the bottom,

00:04:35.070 --> 00:04:37.620
which moved the table up and down.

00:04:37.620 --> 00:04:40.260
The whole facility is massive.

00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:43.080
There is one warehouse where
the shake table is housed,

00:04:43.080 --> 00:04:44.790
but it's in such high demand

00:04:44.790 --> 00:04:46.560
that all the buildings are constructed

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:50.070
in a separate warehouse and
then transferred across.

00:04:50.070 --> 00:04:53.160
Then there is a whole
area full of giant engines

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:56.580
and nitrogen storage tanks
just to power the shake table.

00:04:56.580 --> 00:04:57.413
- [Petr] Oh my God.

00:04:57.413 --> 00:04:59.070
This is a huge engine.

00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:00.000
- [Derek] Using this setup,

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:01.740
the scientists can perfectly simulate

00:05:01.740 --> 00:05:03.120
past earthquakes and determine

00:05:03.120 --> 00:05:05.370
their effects on different buildings.

00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:09.300
The shake table can hold
masses up to 1200 tons

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:10.890
and jolt them with accelerations

00:05:10.890 --> 00:05:13.590
up to 15 meters per second squared.

00:05:13.590 --> 00:05:15.993
That's over one 1.5 gs.

00:05:17.730 --> 00:05:21.480
Now, I know jet fighters can
pull like 10 gs as they turn,

00:05:21.480 --> 00:05:22.980
but it's another story

00:05:22.980 --> 00:05:25.620
if you're in your house and
the floor starts accelerating

00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:27.333
faster than a falling object.

00:05:29.850 --> 00:05:31.170
The goal of the shake table

00:05:31.170 --> 00:05:33.810
is to realistically simulate earthquakes.

00:05:33.810 --> 00:05:36.090
To do this, you need two things.

00:05:36.090 --> 00:05:38.190
A way of being able to apply enough force

00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:41.580
in a precise and controlled
way, and the signal data

00:05:41.580 --> 00:05:43.680
from real earthquakes.

00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:45.793
This is how they do it.

00:05:45.793 --> 00:05:49.380
- Are you okay at high elevation place?

00:05:49.380 --> 00:05:52.230
- Let's see.
(both laughing)

00:05:52.230 --> 00:05:53.640
- This one is actuator.

00:05:53.640 --> 00:05:56.280
- The actuators themselves are hydraulic.

00:05:56.280 --> 00:05:59.130
Inside each one, there's a 30 ton piston

00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:01.380
driven by high pressure oil.

00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:02.940
- This is massive.

00:06:02.940 --> 00:06:04.920
This is, I don't know, a meter,

00:06:04.920 --> 00:06:07.110
meter and a half in diameter.

00:06:07.110 --> 00:06:08.610
- [Derek] But to generate
the pressure needed

00:06:08.610 --> 00:06:10.050
to operate the shake table

00:06:10.050 --> 00:06:12.180
and sustain it for minutes at a time,

00:06:12.180 --> 00:06:15.870
E-Defense needs huge
reserves of pressure storage.

00:06:15.870 --> 00:06:17.880
That's why there's a whole
section of the warehouse

00:06:17.880 --> 00:06:21.390
with massive high pressure
storage tanks full of nitrogen.

00:06:21.390 --> 00:06:26.390
- We have 20 of these lead
spherical shaped accumulators,

00:06:28.550 --> 00:06:31.410
so we accumulate the pressure.

00:06:31.410 --> 00:06:33.750
- To pressurize these
tanks liquid nitrogen

00:06:33.750 --> 00:06:36.900
is pumped in from a large
storage tank outside,

00:06:36.900 --> 00:06:39.750
and as that liquid warms
up, it turns into a gas

00:06:39.750 --> 00:06:44.040
and expands 694 times its original volume.

00:06:44.040 --> 00:06:45.300
It's relatively easy

00:06:45.300 --> 00:06:48.150
to obtain very high
pressures with nitrogen.

00:06:48.150 --> 00:06:49.620
Then when the pressure is needed,

00:06:49.620 --> 00:06:53.250
it's transferred to the oil
using a bunch of pistons.

00:06:53.250 --> 00:06:56.250
As the test runs, the oil
is pumped to the actuators

00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:58.080
by these giant engines,

00:06:58.080 --> 00:07:00.150
but even they can't
sustain the pressure needed

00:07:00.150 --> 00:07:02.490
to operate the shake table for very long.

00:07:02.490 --> 00:07:04.710
And so the nitrogen pressure reserves mean

00:07:04.710 --> 00:07:05.880
that the shake table can deliver

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:07.530
a consistent amount of force

00:07:07.530 --> 00:07:09.813
from the start of the
test right to the end.

00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:14.970
While a test is run, the
pressurized oil needs to be pumped

00:07:14.970 --> 00:07:16.950
to the actuators by the engines.

00:07:16.950 --> 00:07:19.140
The flow to each actuator is controlled

00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:22.500
by electronic servo valves,
meaning precisely timed

00:07:22.500 --> 00:07:24.330
and measured forces can be applied

00:07:24.330 --> 00:07:27.210
to the table to match any earthquake.

00:07:27.210 --> 00:07:30.480
Now, because the actuators can
only move in one dimension,

00:07:30.480 --> 00:07:32.700
if they were fixed directly to the table,

00:07:32.700 --> 00:07:35.460
there would be no flexibility
and they would break.

00:07:35.460 --> 00:07:38.280
And so the engineers at
E-Defense designed bespoke

00:07:38.280 --> 00:07:40.230
seven meter long universal joints

00:07:40.230 --> 00:07:43.230
to transfer the force from the
actuators to the shake table.

00:07:44.430 --> 00:07:46.680
To simulate real earthquakes.

00:07:46.680 --> 00:07:48.720
The shaking can't be random.

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:50.370
I mean, each earthquake has its own

00:07:50.370 --> 00:07:52.320
characteristic pattern of movement,

00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:55.080
which can be recorded using a seismometer.

00:07:55.080 --> 00:07:58.140
Early seismometers were
basically just a pen attached

00:07:58.140 --> 00:08:02.250
to some springs, drawing a line
over a moving roll of paper.

00:08:02.250 --> 00:08:04.200
And when there was an
earthquake, the pen would shake

00:08:04.200 --> 00:08:07.560
and draw out the pattern of
acceleration of that earthquake.

00:08:07.560 --> 00:08:09.390
The trace that was seen on the paper

00:08:09.390 --> 00:08:11.940
is known as a seismograph.

00:08:11.940 --> 00:08:14.250
Nowadays we use geophones.

00:08:14.250 --> 00:08:16.740
A geophone is made from
a coil of wire suspended

00:08:16.740 --> 00:08:19.560
around a magnet all
held together by springs

00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:21.690
when the ground shakes, the springs shake,

00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:24.300
causing the wire to move up
and down over the magnet,

00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:26.040
which generates a current.

00:08:26.040 --> 00:08:29.160
This current is recorded
to produce a seismograph

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:30.090
to get the full picture

00:08:30.090 --> 00:08:32.640
of how the earth's surface
moves in all three dimensions,

00:08:32.640 --> 00:08:34.350
three geophones are needed,

00:08:34.350 --> 00:08:37.083
one oriented in each orthogonal direction.

00:08:38.580 --> 00:08:40.290
The strength of an earthquake is measured

00:08:40.290 --> 00:08:41.820
on the magnitude scale.

00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:42.930
The smallest earthquake

00:08:42.930 --> 00:08:46.530
that humans can feel is about
a billion times less powerful

00:08:46.530 --> 00:08:49.170
than the biggest earthquake ever recorded.

00:08:49.170 --> 00:08:52.260
Because of this, the magnitude
scale is logarithmic.

00:08:52.260 --> 00:08:54.840
An increase of one on the
magnitude scale represents

00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:57.993
a tenfold increase in the
force of the earthquake.

00:08:59.040 --> 00:09:01.440
An earthquake under 2.5
on the magnitude scale

00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:03.450
is imperceptible to humans.

00:09:03.450 --> 00:09:05.910
These happen millions of times every year,

00:09:05.910 --> 00:09:08.640
but can only be detected by geophones.

00:09:08.640 --> 00:09:11.100
Earthquakes higher than
six on the magnitude scale

00:09:11.100 --> 00:09:14.280
can damage buildings, but
occur far less frequently,

00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:17.133
only a few hundred times a year globally.

00:09:18.120 --> 00:09:20.100
The most powerful earthquake ever recorded

00:09:20.100 --> 00:09:22.650
was the great Chilean earthquake of 1960,

00:09:22.650 --> 00:09:25.980
which measured 9.5 on the magnitude scale.

00:09:25.980 --> 00:09:28.980
It killed somewhere
between 1 and 6,000 people

00:09:28.980 --> 00:09:33.450
and caused more than 400 million
US dollars worth of damage.

00:09:33.450 --> 00:09:35.340
But how destructive an earthquake is

00:09:35.340 --> 00:09:37.470
isn't just determined by the magnitude.

00:09:37.470 --> 00:09:40.263
It also matters how
close the epicenter is.

00:09:42.390 --> 00:09:44.580
- Behind me is what was until 2022

00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:47.070
the world's longest suspension bridge.

00:09:47.070 --> 00:09:49.800
The Akashi Kaikyo Bridge connects Honshu,

00:09:49.800 --> 00:09:52.830
the main island of Japan to Awaji Island

00:09:52.830 --> 00:09:55.290
nearly four kilometers away.

00:09:55.290 --> 00:09:57.390
The center span the distance

00:09:57.390 --> 00:10:02.390
