meters and 80 centimeters.

00:10:03.540 --> 00:10:05.670
I'm here because a few
kilometers that way,

00:10:05.670 --> 00:10:09.330
and 16 kilometers
underground was the epicenter

00:10:09.330 --> 00:10:13.770
for the Great Hanshin earthquake of 1995.

00:10:13.770 --> 00:10:15.030
As the earthquake struck,

00:10:15.030 --> 00:10:17.820
the bridge was still under construction.

00:10:17.820 --> 00:10:20.310
And despite being right
above the epicenter,

00:10:20.310 --> 00:10:23.310
there was no major
damage to the structure.

00:10:23.310 --> 00:10:26.520
But the earth underneath
the bridge had moved,

00:10:26.520 --> 00:10:29.670
and the original plans
would no longer work.

00:10:29.670 --> 00:10:32.190
The plans would need to be modified.

00:10:32.190 --> 00:10:35.520
So that's how the world's
longest suspension bridge

00:10:35.520 --> 00:10:38.073
became 80 centimeters longer.

